column5: Holy Moley...  thats a biggun!
Wow, that thing is a *$%&ing monster!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Sweeeeeeeeeet!!!
Wow speechless!!! Congrats, hate to see what that thing would look like at the end of November after putting the feedbag on. Beautiful fish!!!  Cheers, 1leg

Had a couple of days of good muskie fishing with all the different weather systems we had go through here. This is one of the better ones , a solid 50 plus .Sorry for the picture crop,but a muskie guys gotta do,what he's gotta do.   :D  :D  :D  :D
Leviathan!     You may as well sell your stuff & take up golf or gambling! You'll have a hard time topping that sweetheart!
That is just unreal......  Cant wait for my turn at a monster like that.
nice beast!
What a monsterlunge!!!!Now that is a trophy Musky!!!
Wow!! Now THAT'S a BIG FISH!!!!  Congrats on a mighty fine catch!!
Nice one for sure, beauty...
good job there boyz
Noice fish Double L!!!  How much peanut oil would it take to fry up that thing?!!!
WOW!
Very nice!
WOW   Nice fish!!!!!
Fish that I am dreaming of.  Attaboy Larry ... Congrats.
WTG!!  Im sooooooo jealous!!  Sinker
Just a great, great fish Larry. Congrats to you. You know where they live and you're good at what you do. Thanks for sharing that. Give me a hint, was there a steeple left on the cutting room floor?
Thats a NICE one!
Hahahahahahaha!!  Nice Fish tho!
Great fish congrats. I wouldnt be to worried about the crop,I would do the same.
That is one beauty of a muskie! Congrats
A tough one to beat, Larry.  Congratulations!

Very sweet 50" class musky congratz on ya and I also would not worry about croping spots out we dont need to do that here for LSC but if on a small body of water I see nothing wrong with it ler her grow for months and get her again.
Thanks alot guys. Hey Roy , you know you can't take a picture around here without getting a steeple in it.
awesome LUNGE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!....congrats  ....can you imagine the size of that girl when she starts heavily gorging up prey in the fall????
I'd have a heart attack if I saw that thing "lunge" at my bait.  Might I ask what you caught it on?  Congrats to you!
